  "texts": [
    "The study assesses its impact on incident response capabilities and cybersecurity skills development, emphasizing the value of immersive training experiences and knowledge exchange for proactive cybersecurity mindsets and cyber resilience [10].In their study, M. Yamin et al. [11] developed a serious game designed to enhance the development of cyber-security exercise scenarios, addressing the inefficiencies in traditional exercise preparations.",
    "Their study made use of a Domain Specific Language (DSL) and infrastructure coordination which allows users to mimic real-time cybersecurity scenarios as attackers or defenders.",
    "This approach not only streamlines the scenario creation process but also allows for extensive testing in a simulated environment before deployment in realistic settings.",
    "Their proposed method represents a significant advancement in cyber-security training, focusing on operational strategy development and effective scenario modeling.",
    "R. Nakata et al. [12] introduced a Docker-based cyber range system, designed to address the growing need for effective information security education by automatically generating multiple randomized scenarios using Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) techniques [13][14][15]."
  ],
